### Fine-tuning vs. forgetting

A potential dilemma arises when fine-tuning a large language model for specific tasks, as it may result in catastrophic forgetting of its original capabilities. This section explores the extent of forgetting exhibited by CulturePark on BIG-Bench-Hard (BBH) [23], which comprises 21 tasks that assess semantic understanding and logical reasoning. For cost efficiency, we sampled \(100\) samples from each BBH task. We evaluated our models against the baseline model, GPT-3.5-turbo. The results in Figure 5(d) indicate that CulturePark generally maintains or even improves performance on most benchmarks, including the 21 tasks in BBH. This improvement suggests potential latent relationships between cultural data and general benchmarks, implying that fine-tuning of cultural data could improve general reasoning abilities.

